<p>
    In addition, we at Project Intuition have direct access to the contents of the database.  This allows us to make
    adjustments to our modules (as a simple example, if a question is only correctly answered 5% of the time, this 
    tells us the question is too difficult, worded poorly, or confusing for another reason and needs to be re-evaluated).
    Since Project Intuition courses are designed to be taken corequisitely with their associated undergraduate math 
    courses we plan to eventually link our own data to student performance metrics gathered by the instructor of the associated
    in person math course including data such as test scores and class attendance.  In this way we can see if there
    is a correlation between use of our product and improved performance, and, if so, exactly what aspects of our
    product appear to be most helpful.

</p>

<p>
The second type of research that we are engaging in involves reviewing the current literature in the 
field of mathematics education to help inform the construction of our product.  


</p>

